-- American States Water Profit Increases 33%, Helped by Rates
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2013-05-10T15:34:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-10/american-states-water-profit-increases-33-helped-by-rates.html
American States Water Co ., a
California-based water service and electricity provider,
reported first-quarter profit climbed 33 percent to $13.5
million from a year earlier, helped by higher tariffs.  Operating revenue rose 3.4 percent to $110.6 million, the
San Dimas-based utility said today in a statement. American
States Water is the parent of Golden State Water Co. and
American States Utility Services Inc. Its shares have increased
51 percent over the past year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in London at 
